<CENTER>
<H1>&nbsp;</H1>
<H1>Hierarchical Petri Nets</H1>
</CENTER>

<UL><UL><UL> <UL><UL><UL>
  <LI><FONT size=5>Specifications for real systems have a tendency to become large and complex</FONT>
  <LI><FONT size=5>An abstraction mechanism, hierarchical structuring, is used to make constructing,
reviewing, and modifying the model easier</FONT>
  <LI><FONT size=5>The hierarchy construct is called a <FONT color=mediumblue>subnet</FONT></FONT>
  <LI><FONT size=5>A subnet is an aggregate of a number of places, transitions, and subsystems</FONT>
  <LI><FONT size=5>Such a construct can be used to structure large processes</FONT>
  <LI><FONT size=5>Each subnet is represented with a rectangular box that encapsulates part of the
Petri Net model</FONT></LI>
</UL></UL></UL></UL></UL></UL>

